                    <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
                </div>

                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <div class="reveal bg-brand-dark rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-700">
                        <h4 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-brand-green mb-2">Can I pick up the guttering from your workshop?</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                            Because seamless guttering comes in continuous lengths (often 10 meters or more), it is impossible to transport safely on a standard van or roof rack without damaging the profile. That's why our Cut & Drop service brings the extrusion machine directly to your site.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="reveal reveal-delay-100 bg-brand-dark rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-700">
                        <h4 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-brand-green mb-2">Do you supply the brackets and accessories too?</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                            Yes, absolutely. We supply the continuous aluminium lengths along with all the necessary concealed brackets, internal/external corners, stop ends, running outlets, and high-grade sealants required for a complete, professional installation.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="reveal reveal-delay-200 bg-brand-dark rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-700">
                        <h4 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-brand-green mb-2">Is there a minimum order requirement?</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                            Due to the logistics of bringing the mobile machinery to the site, there is generally a minimum meterage requirement for the Cut & Drop service. Please call us to discuss your specific project dimensions and we will provide a clear, upfront quote.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="reveal reveal-delay-300 bg-brand-dark rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-700">
                        <h4 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-brand-green mb-2">How do I cut it if I make a mistake measuring?</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                            Aluminium is easy to work with. If a length needs slight trimming on-site, it can be easily and cleanly cut using standard metal-cutting tools (like tin snips or a fine-toothed hacksaw). However, we always recommend measuring twice so we can extrude the perfect length for you.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-brand-green relative overflow-hidden">
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-brand mix-blend-multiply opacity-90"></div>
